  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">QUESTIONS ON VERB (HAS, HAVE AND HAD)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">When to Use &ldquo;Has&rdquo;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Using &ldquo;Has&rdquo; in the Present Tense<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">With this understanding, the use of &ldquo;has&rdquo; and &ldquo;have&rdquo; will very easy for you.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In the present tense, &ldquo;has&rdquo; is used with the third-person singular point of view. This means that you can use it with<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">he, she, it<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">, a<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">name<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">or a<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">singular noun.<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">It is also only used with<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">affirmative statements.<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">This means that if you are asking a question, or if you&rsquo;re talking in the negative (using the word &ldquo;not&rdquo;), you won&rsquo;t use &ldquo;has.&rdquo;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">He<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">brown eyes.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">She<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">the answer to your question.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">That book<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">400 pages.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Japan<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">amazing food.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Meena<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">45 pencils.<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&ldquo;Has&rdquo; is also used with singular pronouns like &ldquo;everybody,&rdquo; &ldquo;anybody&rdquo; and &ldquo;nobody.&rdquo;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Everybody<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">a copy of the book.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Nobody<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">the answer.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I don&rsquo;t think anybody<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">coffee.<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Using &ldquo;Has&rdquo; as an Auxiliary Verb in the Present Perfect Tense<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">We also use &ldquo;has&rdquo; as an auxiliary verb in the present perfect tense.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Again, this is only in the case of a third-person singular subject:<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">he, she, it<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">, a<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">name<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">or a<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">singular noun.<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">However, in the present perfect tense&mdash;unlike in the present tense&mdash;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">we use &ldquo;has&rdquo; whether we&rsquo;re making a statement or asking a question.<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Also, we use &ldquo;has&rdquo; whether the sentence is<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">affirmative or negative.<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">John<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">gone<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">to California four times. (Affirmative statement)<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">she<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">received<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">the letter? (Affirmative question)<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The dog<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has not eaten<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">today. (Negative statement)<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">he<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">not told<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">you about this? (Negative question)<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">UNN PUTME Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">When his car tyre &hellip;. on the way, he did not know what to do<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(a) has burst (b) had burs (c) bursted (d) burst<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(has burst, 2010\/2011, no 14)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">JAMB Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Long after everyone&hellip;&hellip;. the hall, obi still sat inside. A. left B. is leaving C. has left D. had left<\/span><br><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(has left)<\/span><\/em><br><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">When to use: to have<\/span><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">have<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">a new car.<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The basic meaning of the verb have is &ldquo;to be in the possession of something&rdquo;. It is used in present simple, and it expresses a fact of having something in the present.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">When it comes to auxiliary verb &ldquo;have&rdquo;, we use it to form present perfect and present perfect continuous (read introduction to Tenses for clarification).&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">have<\/span><\/strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">gone to that show already.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In this example, &ldquo;have&rdquo; is used as an auxiliary verb to form present perfect. Present perfect is a tense that connects past and the present. In this example, the person went to the show sometime in the past, but that is still valid in the present.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Auxiliary verb&nbsp;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&ldquo;to have<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&rdquo; is used to express that present through its present form.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">have<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">skipped breakfast today and now I&rsquo;m hungry.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In this example &ldquo;have&rdquo; is again used to form present perfect. Here it expresses a finished action in the past that has a result on the present &ndash; because the person in the example didn&rsquo;t eat breakfast in the morning, in the present the person is hungry. To connect the two, present perfect is used and the verb &ldquo;have&rdquo; again serves as a signal of the present time by being in the present itself (by form).&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">have<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">been going to the same cafe for 10 years.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Auxiliary verb &ldquo;to have&rdquo; is also used to form present perfect continuous. The tense is used to express regularity of some action that started in the past, and continues to happen throughout some amount of<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">time regularly and it is still true in the present. Auxiliary verb helps us to become aware of the present time of the action.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">have<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">been watching that show the whole day.<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In this example have is also used to form present perfect continuous. It expresses and action that started in the past, but was happening the whole time leading up to the present, and continues still. The present form of have reminds us of the present time of the action.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">When to use Has been?<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">That china set<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">been in our family for year.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In this example, we see another form of the verb &ldquo;to have&rdquo;.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&ldquo;Has&rdquo; is the<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">third person singular<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">of the verb to have, used for pronouns he, she, it. In this example, we used it to form present perfect, and has functions the same as &ldquo;have&rdquo; &ndash; it contains and expresses the present time, connects the past and the present.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">He<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">been reading for the past two hours.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In this example has is used to form present perfect continuous. It is used for the same pronouns, he, she or it, so, for the third person singular.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">As we said, as have and has are the same verbs, their function is the same &ndash; has also signaled the present for some action that started in the past, but continues up to the present.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">She<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">has<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">been running for half an hour without any pause.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Has is again used to form present perfect continuous. It expresses an unfinished action that started up in the past<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">continued to happen for some amount of time leading up to the present and is still true in the present.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Has been<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-36pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:8.4pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">He<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">has been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">reading the newspaper for three hours<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-36pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:8.4pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">She<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">has been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">walking a field for two hours.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-36pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:8.4pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">He<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">has been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">traveling in the UK for two months.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-36pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:8.4pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">It<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">has been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">raining since morning.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-36pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:8.4pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Steve Jobs<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">has been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">writing a scientific book for some days.<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Have been<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:22.5pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:3.9pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">have been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">singing an English song two times.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:22.5pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:3.9pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">We<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">have been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">watching a scientific English movie for three hours.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:22.5pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:3.9pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">They<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">have been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">playing the National Football League in the field for two hours.<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:22.5pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:3.9pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Have you been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">completing the assignment for four hours?<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:22.5pt; margin-bottom:8pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; font-family:serif; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; -aw-list-padding-sml:3.9pt;\"><span style=\"font:7pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">have been<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">watching the zone since morning.<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">JAMB Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The words<\/span><u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/u><u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/u><u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/u><u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/u><u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/u><u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/u><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">divided between the end of one line.<\/span><br><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. have been B. have being C. has been D. has being<\/span><br><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(have been)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><br><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The employer, not the salesmen___ responsible for the loss (a) have been (b) was (c) were (d) will be<\/span><br><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(have been)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">When to use had been?<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">had<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">a dress like that,&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Verb &ldquo;had&rdquo; is the past form of the verb to have. It expresses the possession of something in the past, something someone had before, but no longer has, the action is completely in the past.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">He<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">had<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">studied English before he moved to New York.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&ldquo;Had&rdquo; may also be used as an auxiliary verb to form past perfect. When we use past perfect, we express a past action that happened before some other past action, so past before the past.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Auxiliary verb &ldquo;had&rdquo; signals the past by it past form. When it comes to had, it has the same form throughout all persons, so with he, she, it, we also use &ldquo;had&rdquo;, just like with all other person.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">I<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">had<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">gone to that school before I changed cities.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In this example we are again faced with a past action that happened before some other past action. To express that, auxiliary verb &ldquo;had&rdquo; is used.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">He<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">had<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">been waiting there for more than 2 hours when she finally arrived.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Auxiliary verb &ldquo;had&rdquo; is also used to form past perfect continuous. It expresses some past action that was happening for some time in the past, before some other past action happened. To sum up, we use auxiliary verb &ldquo;have&rdquo; to form present perfect and present perfect continuous. &ldquo;Had&rdquo; is the past form of &ldquo;have&rdquo;, and therefore it is used to form past perfect and past perfect continuous.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">UNN PUTME Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1. The rain......when the accident took place.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. has stopped B. stopped C. was stopped D. had stopped<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(Had stopped, 2010\/2011)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">2. Professor Nweke _____ since 1984.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. has been teaching B. has taught C. was teaching D. had been taught<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(has been teaching, 2014\/2015, no 5)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(Gerund<\/span><\/em><strong><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">:&nbsp;<\/span><\/em><\/strong><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The sentence is a present perfect continuous tense. It begins in the past, continuous till the present with the intention to extending into the future. The structure is Subject + has\/have + been + gerund...)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">3. _____ him in the crowd, I would have told you at once.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. Had it been I saw B. if I saw C. Had I seen D. Should I see<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(Had I seen, 2009\/2010, no 14)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">JAMB Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1. Usman would have won the race ....<\/span><br><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. if he had run faster faster B. although he ran faster C. only if he could run fast D. if he had run faster<\/span><br><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(if he had run faster)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">2. Suana&nbsp;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">____<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">that hexagons had five sides, but later he knew they were six-sided figures. (a) would have believed (b) had believed (c) believes (d) has believed<\/span><br><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(had believed<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">)<\/span><br><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">3. The invigilator___ to know how long the examination.... going on.<\/span><br><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A wanted\/has been B wants\/had been C. wants\/have been D. wanted\/had been<\/span><br><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">(wanted\/had been)<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "QUESTIONS ON VERB (HAS, HAVE AND HAD)"
}